<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ISO-8859-1" standalone="no"?> 
<!DOCTYPE MAN SYSTEM "../../man.dtd">
<MAN>
  <LANGUAGE>eng</LANGUAGE>
  <TITLE>sylmX  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE>April 1993  </DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="sylm"> Sylvester matrix  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>[S]=sylm(a,b)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
 <PARAM_INDENT>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>a,b  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : two polynomials
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>S  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : matrix
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
 </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
    <VERB>sylm(a,b)</VERB> gives the Sylvester matrix associated to polynomials
    <VERB>a</VERB> and <VERB>b</VERB>, i.e. the matrix <VERB>S</VERB> such that:
  </P>
  <P>
    <VERB>coeff( a*x + b*y )&apos; = S * [coeff(x)&apos;;coeff(y)&apos;]</VERB>.
  </P>
  <P>
    Dimension of <VERB>S</VERB> is equal to <VERB>degree(a)+degree(b)</VERB>.
  </P>
  <P>
    If <VERB>a</VERB> and <VERB>b</VERB> are coprime polynomials then
  </P>
  <P>
    <VERB>rank(sylm(a,b))=degree(a)+degree(b))</VERB> and the instructions
  </P>
  <VERBATIM><![CDATA[
  u = sylm(a,b) \ eye(na+nb,1)
  x = poly(u(1:nb),'z','coeff')
  y = poly(u(nb+1:na+nb),'z','coeff')
   ]]></VERBATIM>
  <P>
    compute Bezout factors <VERB>x</VERB> and <VERB>y</VERB> of minimal degree 
    such that <VERB>a*x+b*y = 1</VERB>
  </P>
  <P>
  </P>
  <P>
  </P>
  <P>
  </P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
</MAN>
